{% set defaultCode %}<aside>
  <h4>Did you know?</h4>
  <p>The aside element was introduced in HTML5 to provide
  semantic meaning for content that is tangentially
  related to the main content.</p>
</aside>{% endset %}

{% set sidebarCode %}<aside class="sidebar">
  <h4>Quick Links</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#">Getting Started</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Documentation</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">API Reference</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Examples</a></li>
  </ul>
</aside>{% endset %}

{% set noteCode %}<aside class="note">
  <strong>Note:</strong> This feature is available
  in version 2.0 and later.
</aside>{% endset %}

{% set floatCode %}<article>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur
  adipiscing elit...</p>
  <aside class="float">
    <p><em>"Design is not just what it looks like
    and feels like. Design is how it works."</em></p>
    <p>— Steve Jobs</p>
  </aside>
  <p>Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud
  exercitation ullamco laboris...</p>
</article>{% endset %}

  <section>
    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> element for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sidebar navigation or supplementary content</li>
      <li>Pull quotes that highlight key text from an article</li>
      <li>Related links or "See also" sections</li>
      <li>Advertising or promotional content</li>
      <li>Glossary definitions or explanatory boxes</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Content in an aside should be related to the surrounding content but not essential to understanding it. The page should make sense if the aside is removed.</p>
    <p><strong>For alert-style notifications</strong> (warnings, tips, success messages, errors), use <a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/status-message/"><code>&lt;status-message&gt;</code></a> instead.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <h3>Default</h3>
    <p>Basic aside without additional styling.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/aside-default.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/aside/default" title="Default aside" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Default aside">{{ defaultCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.sidebar</h3>
    <p>Panel style with background for sidebar layouts.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/aside-sidebar.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/aside/sidebar" title="Sidebar aside" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Sidebar aside">{{ sidebarCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.note</h3>
    <p>Subtle note style for minor supplementary information.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/aside-note.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/aside/note" title="Note aside" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Note aside">{{ noteCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.float</h3>
    <p>Floating aside for pull quotes that flow with text.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/aside-float.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/aside/float" title="Float aside" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Float aside">{{ floatCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.sidenote</h3>
    <p>Margin annotation that floats alongside text on wide viewports. On narrow viewports, collapses to a bordered inline block. Requires the parent container to have margin space (e.g., inside <code>&lt;layout-text&gt;</code>).</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/examples/demos/sidenote-css.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/aside/sidenote" title="Sidenote" shadow></browser-window>

    <aside class="note">
      <strong>Tip:</strong> For automated sidenotes with numbering and progressive enhancement, use <a href="/docs/elements/web-components/footnotes/"><code>&lt;foot-notes data-mode="sidenotes"&gt;</code></a> instead. The <code>.sidenote</code> class is for manual, CSS-only placement.
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Variants</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Class</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.sidebar</code></td>
          <td>Raised background panel style for sidebar content</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.note</code></td>
          <td>Subtle, compact note with muted text for de-emphasized content</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.float</code></td>
          <td>Floats to the right with max-width of 40% for pull quotes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.sidenote</code></td>
          <td>Margin annotation (22ch) that floats alongside text; collapses to bordered block on narrow viewports</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Aside creates a complementary landmark that screen readers can navigate to</li>
      <li>Include a heading to label the aside content, especially for longer asides</li>
      <li>Keep aside content concise and focused on a single topic</li>
      <li>Floating asides should use <code>clear: both</code> on following content to prevent layout issues</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
